#include <composed.h>
%zone lostlands
title "Lost Lands"

lifespan 20
reset RESET_ANYHOW
creators {"cabal"}
notes
"
Created by Cabal: Previous to his departure
Updated: January 1996 by Isildur - added dil to Ptha and
Quetzal, in effect making the quest work."


%rooms
/*---------------------- JUNGLE RIVER --------------------*/

			landslide
names {"landslide"}
title "A recent landslide"
descr
"     The steep slope of the mountain side has been recently cleared by a
landslide. You gasp as you survey the huge valley that has opened up to the
south. A small river runs across the valley through the teeming jungle, part
of which has been squashed by the landslide. Fires to the southwest send
columns of smoke into the air, and a stone pyramid breaks through the jungle
canopy to the south east on the other side of the river."
movement SECT_MOUNTAIN
north to mnt_pass@ratswarf;
south to sqsh_jungle;
end

			sqsh_jungle
names {"squashed jungle", "jungle"}
title "A squashed jungle"
descr
"     This area of  jungle has been crushed by tons of rock crashing down
from the mountain to the north. An occasional frond of a squashed plant comes
jutting up between the boulders. A path leads into the jungle to the south.
Someone has recently planted a sign here among the rocks."
movement SECT_MOUNTAIN
north to landslide;
south to jungle1;
extra {"sign"}
"                        CITIZENS OF THE KINGDOM
Greetings from King Welmar. Due to the increasing number of citizens choosing
to adventure in these strange lost lands, the King has established an embassy
outside the native village. If you encounter any problems beyond the
embassy's province, contact Cabal the Zombie (who seems to know more about
this place than anyone).  Good travels.
"
end

			jungle1
names {"jungle trail"}
title "A jungle trail"
descr
"     You are on the edge of a dark jungle on a narrow new trail. To the
north, the jungle has been squashed by a recent landslide. The path continues,
through thick vegetation, to the east."
movement SECT_SWAMP
OUT_DARK_NON_NOON
north to sqsh_jungle;
east to jungle2;
end

			jungle2
names {"jungle fork"}
title "A fork in the jungle."
descr
"     Long vines hang down from the high trees here where a new path through
the jungle is intersected by an animal trail leading north.  You can hear the
sound of the jungle river nearby."
movement SECT_SWAMP
OUT_DARK_NON_NOON
west to jungle1;
east to river_edge;
north to jungle3;
end

			jungle3
names {"animal trail"}
title "An animal trail through the jungle."
descr
"     You are on a narrow animal trail through the deep jungle. To the south,
the trail opens into a larger path, while to the east it crosses over a
stagnant pool. The plants are thick, and the ground is twisted with their
roots."
movement SECT_SWAMP
OUT_DARK_NON_NOON
south to jungle2;
east to disease_p;
end
			jungle4
names {"animal trail"}
title "An animal trail through the jungle."
descr
"     The faint animal trail continues to wind through the dense jungle
foliage. To the west, it crosses by a pool of stagnant water, while to
the south it seems to end in a cluster of trees. It appears lighter to
the south."
movement SECT_SWAMP
OUT_DARK_NON_NOON
south to monkey_nest;
west to disease_p;
east to kali_gard;
SECRET_DOOR_DIFFICULTY (EAST, 40)
end

			disease_p
names {"stagnant pool", "pool"}
title "A stagnant pool"
descr
"     The animal trail, running fairly straight east and east through the
jungle, comes along the edge of a large stagnant pool. The water stands only
three inches deep, but fills the impressions between the strong roots of the
jungle trees. It doesn't look like it is going to drain anytime soon.."
movement SECT_SWAMP
OUT_DARK_NON_NOON
west to jungle3;
east to jungle4;
end
			monkey_nest
names {"monkey nest", "nest"}
title "A monkey nest in the jungle"
descr
"     You have stumbled into a monkey nest at the base of a group of tall
jungle trees. Many small monkeys scatter into the trees screaming alarm. The
foliage is too thick in this part of the jungle to move through, although a
small animal trail leads away to the north. It looks like you could climb up
one of the jungle trees here."
movement SECT_SWAMP
OUT_DARK_NON_NOON
north to jungle4;
up to up_monkeynest;
end

			river_edge
names {"river edge", "edge"}
title "Edge of a Jungle River"
descr
"     The trail ends suddenly at the muddy banks of a slow moving stagnant
river through the jungle. You can see across the river to the southern shore,
but can tell that river is too deep to cross on foot.  A path disappears into
the thick underbrush to the west."
movement SECT_SWAMP
west to jungle2;
south to river1;
end

			river1
names {"jungle river"}
title "A river through the thick jungle."
descr
"     You are on a languid, stagnant river through the thick jungle. A little
more light reaches you here, breaking through the thinner canopy hanging over
the river. To the north you see where a trail intersects the river. The river
flows from the west to the east."
movement SECT_WATER_SAIL
special SFUN_FORCE_MOVE
"lostlands/river2!The river's currents pull you down stream." time WAIT_SEC*120 bits SFB_RANTIME
north to river_edge;
east to river2;
west to river7;
end
			river2
names {"jungle river"}
title "A river through the thick jungle."
descr
"     The river continues to flow east through the thick jungle. The stagnant
water is becoming cleaner add the constant rainfall from the forest canopy
mixes in."
movement SECT_WATER_SAIL
special SFUN_FORCE_MOVE
"lostlands/river3!The river's currents pull you down stream." time WAIT_SEC*90 bits SFB_RANTIME
east to river3;
west to river1;
end

			river3
names {"jungle river"}
title "A river through the thick jungle."
descr
"     The canopy of trees is starting to close in again, forming almost a
tunnel of jungle life with the river running through it. To the east, the
river takes a sharp bend north."
movement SECT_WATER_SAIL
special SFUN_FORCE_MOVE
"lostlands/river4!The river's currents pull you down stream." time WAIT_SEC*90 bits SFB_RANTIME
east to river4;
west to river2;
end

			river4
names {"jungle river"}
title "A turn in the jungle river."
descr
"     The river flows faster here, picking up speed as it flows from the
west to north. To the north, the jungle canopy keeps out almost all light.
There is a crude wooden boat dock to the south among the thick foliage."
movement SECT_WATER_SAIL
special SFUN_FORCE_MOVE
"lostlands/river5!The river's currents pull you down stream." time WAIT_SEC*70 bits SFB_RANTIME
north to river5;
west to river3;
south to tribal_dock;
end
			river5
names {"jungle river"}
title "A jungle river"
descr
"     The jungle canopy has closed over the river as it flows north. The
current is continuing to pick up speed. You can see a crude boat dock
upstream to the south."
movement SECT_WATER_SAIL
OUT_DARK_NON_NOON
special SFUN_FORCE_MOVE
"lostlands/river6!The river's currents pull you down stream." time WAIT_SEC*40 bits SFB_RANTIME
north to river6;
south to river4;
end

			river6
names {"jungle river"}
title "A jungle river"
descr
"     The current is becoming quite fierce now on this river. To the north,
it appears that the river spins into some kind of whirlpool! Perhaps you
should paddle south back up stream."
movement SECT_WATER_SAIL
OUT_DARK_NON_NOON
special SFUN_FORCE_MOVE
"lostlands/whirlpool!You are drawn into the whirlpool." time WAIT_SEC*40 bits SFB_RANTIME
north to whirlpool;
south to river5;
end

			whirlpool
names {"whirlpool"}
title "A whirlpool"
descr
"     You have been sucked into the whirlpool! You fight hard to keep control
of your craft, but it appears there is no escape. You are being sucked down
the whirlpool into some kind of underground rapids."
movement SECT_WATER_SAIL
OUT_ALWAYS_DARK
special SFUN_FORCE_MOVE
"lostlands/tun_rapid!You are swept underground." time WAIT_SEC*30 bits SFB_RANTIME
end

			tun_rapid
names {"tunnel rapids"}
title "Underground tunnel rapids."
descr
"     Everything is a confusion of bubbles, swirling waters and panic. You
try to keep the boat from hitting the narrow walls of this underground tunnel
as the current sweeps you further down."
movement SECT_WATER_SAIL
OUT_ALWAYS_DARK
special SFUN_FORCE_MOVE
"lostlands/tun_rapid2!You are swept along by the rapids." time WAIT_SEC*20 bits SFB_RANTIME
end

			tun_rapid2
names {"tunnel rapids"}
title "Underground tunnel rapids."
descr
"     The stream continues to drop into the earth, turning back upon itself
time and time again. You have lost all sense of direction and are fighting
to keep the boat from crashing to bits!"
movement SECT_WATER_SAIL
OUT_ALWAYS_DARK
special SFUN_FORCE_MOVE
"lostlands/tun_rapid3!You are swept along by the rapids." time WAIT_SEC*16 bits SFB_RANTIME
end

			tun_rapid3
names {"tunnel rapids"}
title "Underground tunnel rapids."
descr
"     After another bend in the underground rapids, you are now on a
straightaway and you feel safer. The tunnel ceiling is less than a foot above
your head. Suddenly, you notice that the stream is heading towards a fast
underground waterfall, tumbling even deeper into the earth. You hang on
tightly to your boat and pray that you survive the plummet."
movement SECT_WATER_SAIL
OUT_ALWAYS_DARK
special SFUN_FORCE_MOVE
"ww1/undergr_lake!You are swept over the waterfall!" time WAIT_SEC*20 bits SFB_RANTIME
end

			river7
names {"jungle river"}
title "A river through the thick jungle."
descr
"     The river begins to grow wider here and looks even more stagnant, full
of algae and muck. You begin to notice subtle changes in the jungle landscape,
such as ferns growing on the riverbed. The river flows from west to east."
movement SECT_WATER_SAIL
special SFUN_FORCE_MOVE
"lostlands/river1!The river's currents pull you down stream." time WAIT_SEC*120 bits SFB_RANTIME
north to river_edge;
east to river1;
west to river8;
end


			river8
names {"jungle river"}
title "A bend in the jungle river"
descr
"     The stagnant river bed is surround by tall ginkgo trees and thick ferns
with long willowy arms. To the south, the river opens into a huge delta
draining from a strange swamp."
movement SECT_WATER_SAIL
special SFUN_FORCE_MOVE
"lostlands/river7!The river's currents pull you down stream." time WAIT_SEC*120 bits SFB_RANTIME
east to river7;
south to swamp_drain;
end

			swamp_drain
names {"swamp drain", "swamp"}
title "The primordal swamp delta"
descr
"     This swampy delta, sprinkled with strange giant ferns and scaly ginkgo
trees, feeds a jungle river flowing north. To the south, you see the beginning
of a wide primordal swamp. You can see huge shadows moving through the swamp.

A sign has been recently placed here."
movement SECT_SWAMP
north to river8;
south to pri_swamp1;
extra {"sign"}
" The sign, in large letter, proclaims:
	    W A R N I N G
	 Dinosaur Crossing
      (Recommended Level 50+)"
end

			kali_gard
names {"kali garden"}
title "A strange jungle garden"
descr
"     You have stepped from the jungle trail into a carefully cultivated
garden. Tall bushes in rows lead from the jungle in the west to a strange
crypt in south. The bushes release a sweet herbal aroma. Someone has
obviously been taking good care of these grounds: the plants all seem free
of insects and disease. There is a bronze plaque mounted in the ground here."
movement SECT_SWAMP
ALWAYS_LIGHT
west to jungle4;
south to cabal_lair;
extra {"plaque"}
"
     THE CRYPY GARDEN OF CABAL
	Do Not Pick the Buds
"
end

			cabal_lair
names {"cabals lair"}
title "Crypt in the strange garden"
descr
"     You have stumbled upon a white marble crypt surrounded by strange,
aromatic bushes. The crypt bears no birthdate, but has a long list of death
dates. A small statue by the crypt bears the names of fallen companions. It's
list is also rather long! The garden continues north."
movement SECT_FIELD
ALWAYS_LIGHT
north to kali_gard;
end


/*-------------------- TREE TOP MAZE --------------------*/

			up_monkeynest
names {"above monkey nest", "monkey nest"}
title "Above the monkey's nest"
descr
"     Looking down through the branches of this huge jungle tree, you can see
the nests of a colony of monkeys. It would be an easy climb down to the jungle
from here, or it looks like a vine to the east would be strong enough to carry
your weight."
movement SECT_MOUNTAIN
down to monkey_nest;
east to vine_1;
extra {"vine"}
"It looks like you could just step east and grab the vine on the way!"
end

			banyan_tree
names {"banyan tree", "tree"}
title "High in a banyan tree"
descr
"     You are high in the branches of a banyan tree above the jungle. You are
too high to drop back into the jungle, but strong vines lie to the south and
east."
movement SECT_MOUNTAIN
south to vine_1;
east to vine_3;
extra {"vine"}
"It looks like you could just step out and grab a vine on the way!"
end

			ginkgo_tree
names {"ginkgo tree", "tree"}
title "High in a ginkgo tree"
descr
"     You are high above the jungle on the scaly branches of a massive ginkgo
tree. Below you, you can see a river running through the jungle. A massive
vine, strong enough to support your weight, lies to the north."
movement SECT_MOUNTAIN
north to vine_3;
extra {"vine"}
"It looks like you could just step north and grab the vine on the way!"
end

			herbal_tree
names {"herbal tree", "tree"}
title "High in a herbal tree"
descr
"     Clinging to the branches of this huge, sweet-smelling tree, is easy
since it seems to be slightly sticky. In fact, you could climb either up or
down its trunk, or swing away on a vine to the east."
movement SECT_MOUNTAIN
up to jungle_top;
down to kali_gard;
east to vine_4;
extra {"vine"}
"It looks like you could just step west and grab the vine on the way!"
end

			jungle_top
names {"jungle top"}
title "High above the jungle canopy"
descr
"     You have broken above the jungle canopy, standing in a particularly
dense and sticky batch of sweet-smelling leaves. The tree tops spread away in
all directions like soft rolling green hills. You can see all kinds of birds
and animals moving about the tree tops. You could climb back down into the
foliage of the sweet-smelling tree."
movement SECT_MOUNTAIN
down to herbal_tree;
end

			tzan_porch
names {"jungle porch", "porch"}
title "A platform in the trees"
descr
"     You are on a platform made of wood, high in the trees of the jungle.
A small rope ladder leads up into the trees, although the leaves are too thick
for you to see where it leads. A sturdy vine that looks strong enough to bear
your weight lies to the south."
movement SECT_CITY
south to vine_3;
up to tzan_house;
extra {"vine"}
"It looks like you could just step south and grab the vine on the way!"
extra {"ladder"}
"The rope ladder, crudely made but strong, leads up."
end

			tzan_house
names {"tarzan's house", "house"}
title "Tarzan's jungle house"
descr
"     This small wooden house high in the jungle trees is obviously the home
of the King of Jungle! The main give-away is that most of the stuff in this
this jungle home bears little labels saying 'Universal Studios: Prop Depart-
ment.' A small rope ladder leads down to a platform in the trees, and another
of those strong vines that Tarzan loves so much leads to the north."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
movement SECT_CITY
north to vine_4;
down to tzan_porch;
extra {"vine"}
"It looks like you could just step north and grab the vine on the way!"
extra {"ladder"}
"The rope ladder, crudely made but strong, leads down."
end

			vine_1
names {"vine"}
title "High in the jungle, swinging on a vine"
descr
"    This thick jungle vine is too narrow to crawl up or down, but it looks
like you could swing west to above a monkey nest in the trees, or north into
the branches of a huge banyan tree."
movement SECT_MOUNTAIN
west to up_monkeynest;
north to banyan_tree;
end

			vine_3
names {"vine"}
title "High in the jungle, swinging on a vine"
descr
"    This thick jungle vine is too narrow to crawl up or down, but it looks
like you could swing west into a banyan tree, south into a scaly ginkgo tree
or north onto some kind of platform high in the trees."
movement SECT_MOUNTAIN
west to banyan_tree;
north to tzan_porch;
south to ginkgo_tree;
end

			vine_4
names {"vine"}
title "High in the jungle, swinging on a vine"
descr
"    This thick jungle vine is too narrow to crawl up or down, but it looks
like you could swing west into a huge herbal tree or south into a high tree
house in jungle."
movement SECT_MOUNTAIN
west to herbal_tree;
south to tzan_house;
end


/*-------------------- JUNGLE VILLAGE --------------------*/


			tribal_dock
names {"village dock", "dock"}
title "Village dock"
descr
"     You are on a primitive wooden boat dock on the south bank of the river,
surrounded by thick jungle. A worn trail leads east towards a tall wall of
sharpened logs."
movement SECT_CITY
north to river4;
east to worn_trail;
end

			worn_trail
names {"trail to village","worn trail", "trail"}
title "Worn trail to village"
descr
"     You are on a short worn trail in the jungle. A primitive boat dock on
the river lies to the west and the path leads to a large wooden gate to the
east."
movement SECT_CITY
west to tribal_dock;
east to out_wd_gate;
end

			out_wd_gate
names {"outside wooden gate", "outside gate"}
title "Outside the wooden gate"
descr
"     You are standing outside the large wooden gate of the jungle village.
The village lies to the south. A worn path leads back into the jungle to the
west. You can see some small farms to the east along the village. A large,
grey tent has been pitched to the north, right outside the gate."
movement SECT_CITY
north to embassy;
east to farm1;
west to worn_trail;
south to in_wd_gate open {EX_OPEN_CLOSE,EX_CLOSED} keyword {"gate"};
ALWAYS_LIGHT
extra {"tent"}
"The tent made from animal skins, is very large and bears the
seal of King Welmar - a welcome sight in these strange parts."
end

			embassy
names {"embassy", "king's embassy"}
title "The King's embassy"
descr
"     You are inside the large tent, standing in a well-appointed room.
Although the tent is decorated in the latest styles of Midgaard, the heat and
humidity of the jungle keep this place from seeming truly civilized. Tent
flaps lead east west."
extra {"flaps"}
"The flaps, left open, flutter slightly showing you the way
out of the tent."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
movement SECT_INSIDE
south to out_wd_gate;
east to emb_shrine;
west to ambas_qtrs;
ALWAYS_LIGHT
end

			emb_shrine
names {"embassy shrine", "jungle shrine"}
title "The shrine to Odin"
descr
"     This end of the tent has been decorated with holy symbols and icons of
Odin. Although lacking the serenity of the temples found in more civilized
lands, you can feel the hand of Odin on this place. A tent flap leads west."
extra {"flap"}
"The flap flutters slighty showing the way out of the tent."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_MOB, UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
flags {UNIT_FL_SACRED}
movement SECT_INSIDE
west to embassy;
ALWAYS_LIGHT
end

			ambas_qtrs
names {"ambassador's quarters"}
title "The ambassador's quarters"
descr
"     Although this is obviously the living quarter's of the King's ambassador,
it looks little better than some of the camps you've pitched in the wilderness.
A tent flap leads back from this poor chamber into the main embassy tent."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_MOB, UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
movement SECT_INSIDE
east to embassy;
ALWAYS_LIGHT
end

			farm1
names {"jungle farm", "small farm"}
title "A small farm"
descr
"    You have wandered into a small area cleared from the jungle, which is
being farmed by the jungle tribe. The village wall, made of sharpened wooden
poles, runs along the south. You can see more farmland to the east, and the
wooden gate sits to the west."
movement SECT_FIELD
west to out_wd_gate;
east to farm2;
end

			farm2
names {"jungle farm", "small farm"}
title "A small farm"
descr
"    You have wandered into a small area cleared form the jungle, which is
being farmed by the jungle tribe. The village wall, made of sharpened wooden
poles, runs along the south. You can see more farmland to the west."
movement SECT_FIELD
west to farm1;
SECRET_DOOR_DIFFICULTY (DOWN, 40)
end


			in_wd_gate
names {"inside wooden gate", "inside gate"}
title "Inside the wooden gate"
descr
"    You are inside the wooden gate of the jungle village, which leads north
back into the jungle. The muddy ground of the village turns into a drier
village commons to the south."
movement SECT_CITY
north to out_wd_gate open {EX_OPEN_CLOSE, EX_CLOSED} keyword {"gate"};
south to trib_common;
ALWAYS_LIGHT
end

			trib_common
names {"tribal village commons", "tribal commons"}
title "Tribal village commons"
descr
"    On slightly higher ground than the rest of the jungle village, the ground
of this commons is hard and dry. To the north you can see the wooden gate. To
south, at the base of a tall pyramid, you see the bustle of the tribal
commons. You can here a loud tribal beat coming from a huge hut to the east.
Strange lights flicker from it's wide doorway."
movement SECT_CITY
north to in_wd_gate;
south to trib_square;
east to tribe_disco;
ALWAYS_LIGHT
end

			tribe_disco
names {"stewpot", "tribal", "hut"}
title "The Cannibal's Stewpot"
descr
"    You have entered a huge hut in a jungle decor. Massive
feather and bone decorations, complete with palm trees, give the place a
campy atmosphere. tribal drum beats and chants make the flashy
dance floor look even more exciting. There is sign hanging over
the bar with additional markings on it."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
movement SECT_CITY
west to trib_common;
ALWAYS_LIGHT
extra {"markings","sign"}
"The sign says is big letters, 'FREE DRINKS'. Under that, written
in magic marker:
'These natives haven't caught on to the idea of the barter
system too well. I keep telling them they have to SELL the
drinks, but they will figure that out soon enough. Enjoy the
free drinks while you can.

-Cabal'"
extra {"dance floor", "dance"}
"The dance floor is made up of dirt packed hard from the many
dancing feet that use it."
end

			trib_square
names {"tribal village square", "tribal square"}
title "Tribal village square"
descr
"    You are standing in a great flagstoned square in the jungle village.
To the north you see the village commons. A large brick road leads towards a
bronze gate to the east while a muddy path leads to the west to even larger
gold gate.  To south, built at the base of the massive pyramid, is a cruder
wooden building."
movement SECT_CITY
south to pyrm_entry;
east to brick_road;
west to muddy_path;
north to trib_common;
ALWAYS_LIGHT
end

			brick_road
names {"tribal brick road", "brick road"}
title "Tribal brick road"
descr
"     This thick brick road was obviously not built by the jungle natives.
It looks like it could be as old as the pyramid that looms over the village
somewhere to the south.  The bustle of the tribal square are west and the
bronze gates are east.  A small wooden hut sits to the south of the road,
while a sturdier clay building has been erected to the north."
movement SECT_CITY
north to clay_bldg;
south to wood_hut;
east to in_brnze_gate;
west to trib_square;
ALWAYS_LIGHT
end

			in_brnze_gate
names {"inside bronze gate", "inside gate"}
title "Inside the bronze gate"
descr
"You are just west of the bronze village gate.  On the other side of the gate
you see a sloping path that enters a jungle valley.  A brick road heads west
from here towards the village square.
Small wooden huts have been built to the north and south of here."
movement SECT_CITY
west to brick_road;
south to wood_hut2;
north to wood_hut3;
east to entry2@cthulu descr
"You see a Jungle valley.";
ALWAYS_LIGHT
end

			clay_bldg
names {"clay building"}
title "Inside a clay building"
descr
"     You are inside a sturdy clay building supported by wood beams. Although
sturdier in construction then the other wooden structures in the village, it
is obviously inferior to the workmanship of the Pyramid. A doorway leads south
to the brick road."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
movement SECT_INSIDE
south to brick_road;
ALWAYS_LIGHT
end

			wood_hut
names {"wooden hut"}
title "Inside a wooden hut"
descr
"    You are in a small wooden hut, strewn with the belongings of an entire
village family. The doorway leads north to the brick road."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
movement SECT_INSIDE
north to brick_road;
ALWAYS_LIGHT
end

			wood_hut2
names {"wooden hut"}
title "Inside a wooden hut"
descr
"    You are in a small wooden hut, strewn with the belongings of an entire
village family. The doorway leads north to inside the bronze gate."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
movement SECT_INSIDE
north to in_brnze_gate;
ALWAYS_LIGHT
end

			wood_hut3
names {"wooden hut"}
title "Inside a wooden hut"
descr
"    You are in a small wooden hut, strewn with the belongings of an entire
village family. The doorway leads south to inside the bronze gate."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
movement SECT_INSIDE
south to in_brnze_gate;
ALWAYS_LIGHT
end

			muddy_path
names {"tribal muddy path", "muddy path"}
title "Tribal muddy path"
descr
"    You are on a small, muddy, but well-cleaned path, leading from inside the
golden gate to the west to the village square to the east. To south, a hut
sits upon huge stilts."
movement SECT_CITY
east to trib_square;
west to in_gold_gate;
south to under_hut;
ALWAYS_LIGHT
end

			in_gold_gate
names {"inside golden gate", "inside gate"}
title "Inside the golden gate"
descr
"    You are inside the golden gates of the jungle village, which lead west
into the jungle. You can hear strange howlings and insect sounds coming from
behind the gate. A muddy path leads east toward the village square."
movement SECT_CITY
east to muddy_path;
west to out_gold_gate key serp_key open {EX_OPEN_CLOSE, EX_CLOSED, EX_LOCKED}
keyword {"gate"};
east to muddy_path;
ALWAYS_LIGHT
end


			under_hut
names {"under hut"}
title "Under the Hut"
descr
"    You underneath a wooden hut on stilts. A ladder leads up into the hut
with thick tangled bushes to the west and a wooden fence to the east and
south."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
movement SECT_FIELD
up to doc_hut;
north to muddy_path;
west to doc_gard1;
end
			doc_gard1
names {"strange garden"}
title "The strange jungle garden"
descr
"    You are in a strange and wondrous garden in the jungle village. The
tribal witch doctor obviously uses this cultivated area to grow strange
medical and magical plants. Through thick bushes to the east you can see
the witch doctor's hut and the garden path leads south, with a small wooden
sign beside it."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
movement SECT_FIELD
east to under_hut;
south to doc_gard2;
extra {"sign"}
"BEWARE: Man-Eating Plants"
end

			doc_gard2
names {"strange garden"}
title "The strange jungle garden"
descr
"    This back corner of the witch doctor's garden is choked with huge weeds
and vines and other less savory plants. A small garden trail leads north
past a huge pile of fertilizer."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
movement SECT_FIELD
north to doc_gard1;
extra {"fertilizer", "pile"}
"This huge pile of fertilizer looks like it was made from flesh of
some sort. Perhaps this is what becomes of all those human
sacrifices!"
end


			doc_hut
names {"witch doctor's hut", "hut"}
title "The witch doctor's hut"
descr
"    This wooden hut has a fine view of the entire jungle village, including
the impressive stone pyramid east of here.  The hut is strewn with strange
herbs and magic symbols and has a strong musky odor, like death. A ladder
leads down to the ground."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
movement SECT_INSIDE
down to under_hut;
ALWAYS_LIGHT
end

			pyrm_entry
names {"pyramid entry", "entry"}
title "The pyramid entry"
descr
"    You are in a crude wooden structure, built to serve as an entry to the
huge stone pyramid to the south. North of here, you see the bustle of the
village square. To the south you see a large audience hall."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
movement SECT_INSIDE
north to trib_square;
south to chief_hall;
ALWAYS_LIGHT
end

			chief_hall
names {"chief's hall"}
title "The Chief's Hall"
descr
"    You are in the audience hall of the tribal chief. This weak wooden
structure ends to the south, opening into a courtyard at the base of the
pyramid. To the north the building leads towards the village square."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
movement SECT_INSIDE
north to pyrm_entry;
south to pyrm_court;
ALWAYS_LIGHT
end

			pyrm_court
names {"pyramid courtyard", "pyramid base", "courtyard"}
title "Courtyard before the pyramid"
descr
"    You are in a huge stone courtyard at the base of the pyramid.  A crude
wooden wall surrounds the courtyard, blocking all possible exits except north
into the chief's audience chamber and up the pyramid."
movement SECT_FIELD
north to chief_hall;
up to pyrm_stairs;
ALWAYS_LIGHT
extra {"pyramid"}
" The stone pyramid looms 50 cubits tall and is built of huge stone bricks. It is of
sophisticated design and looks like it has stood forever. Stairs
ascend steeply to the plaza at the structure's top, upon which you see some
kind of altar."
end

			out_gold_gate
names {"outside golden gate", "outside gate"}
title "Outside the golden gate"
descr
"    You are standing outside a golden gate leading into the jungle village.
The primordal jungle stretches off the the west. A deep gully, following
along the village walls of sharpened logs, lies to the north. You could
definitely slide down it, but would not able to climb back up.
A sign has been recently placed here."
movement SECT_FIELD
west to pri_jungle5;
north to pri_gully1;
east to in_gold_gate key serp_key open {EX_OPEN_CLOSE, EX_CLOSED, EX_LOCKED} keyword {"gate"};
ALWAYS_LIGHT
extra {"sign"}
"The sign proclaims in large letters:
	   W A R N I N G
	Dinosaur Crossing
     Suggested Level over 50"
end


/*------------------- The Pyramid ---------------------*/

			pyrm_stairs
names {"pyramid stairs"}
title "The pyramid stairs"
descr
"    These stairs ascending in the side of the pyramid are so steep that they
leave you out of breath! You are about halfway up the side of the pyramid. You
can climb further up to the top of the pyramid, or back down to the courtyard
at the base."
movement SECT_MOUNTAIN
down to pyrm_court;
up to pyrm_top;
end

			pyrm_top
names {"pyramid top", "sacrificial altar"}
title "The pyramid top"
descr
"    Standing at the top of you stone pyramid gives you a great view of the
entire jungle village, out over the walls of sharpened logs to the jungles
and marshes surrounding it. A sacrificial altar is set into the stone here,
with long furrows to drain the blood into a shaft dropping into the pyramid.
The stairs down the pyramid lie to the north."
movement SECT_INSIDE
down to shaft open {EX_OPEN_CLOSE};
north to pyrm_stairs;
end

			shaft
names {"pyramid shaft", "shaft"}
title "the pyramid shaft"
descr
"    You are in a rough stone shaft dropping straight down into the pyramid.
The walls are coated in blood, much of it dried, but some of it still moist to
the touch."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
movement SECT_INSIDE
up to pyrm_top;
down to base_shaft;
extra {"blood"}
"It looks like a mixture of blood poured down the shaft and some kind of blood
oozing from the very rock"
end

			base_shaft
names {"base of shaft", "shaft"}
title "the base of the shaft"
descr
"    Light streams down a rough stone shaft into this large blood-splashed
chamber. You cannot imagine how many people must have been sacrificed on the
pyramid altar to have left this much blood. A large door with a strange lock
leads west."
movement SECT_INSIDE
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
up to shaft;
west to mosaic1 key pyrm_key open {EX_OPEN_CLOSE, EX_LOCKED, EX_PICKPROOF} keyword {"door"};
extra {"lock"}
"The lock looks like it would take a massive pyramid-shaped key to open."
extra {"door"}
"This is obviously the main door into the pyramid, although how you are going
to get the door open is anyone's guess."
end

			mosaic1
names {"mosaic hall"}
title "A small mosaic room."
descr
"    You are in a small, cramped chamber whose walls are decorated with
strange mosaics of half-animal monsters drinking the blood from human corpses.
A large door with a massive lock blocks the way to the east, and this small
hall empties into a larger room to the south."
movement SECT_INSIDE
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_TELEPORT, UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
east to base_shaft key pyrm_key open {EX_OPEN_CLOSE, EX_LOCKED, EX_PICKPROOF} keyword {"east door", "door"};
south to gold_hall;
extra {"lock"}
"The lock looks like it would take a massive pyramid-shaped key to open."
extra {"door"}
"This is obviously the main door into the pyramid, although how you are going
to get the door open is anyone's guess."
extra {"mosaic"}
"The mosaics show a half-snake woman drinking the blood from a pile of human
corpses, all intricately made from tiny pieces of broken glass."
end

			gold_hall
names {"gold hall"}
title "A broad golden hall."
descr
"    The bricks of this grand hall are coated in beaten gold. Dim light from
flickering eternal brazers send flashes of light bouncing off the reflective
walls.  In the middle of the room, a small font of blood sits bubbling. A
sturdy wooden ladder leads up through the frescoed ceiling, and a door leads
west.  To the north, the golden hall turns into a small, mosaic chamber."
movement SECT_INSIDE
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_TELEPORT, UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
west to spot_garden open {EX_OPEN_CLOSE} keyword {"door"};
north to mosaic1;
up to enscroll_room;
extra {"font", "blood"}
"You think about the blood and whether or not you should drink some. Then,
seeing all the small flying insect laying eggs into the blood makes you think
again."
extra {"gold"}
"You hold a torch up to the gold. Yep, it's real. But you have no idea of how
to get it of the bricks."
extra {"ladder"}
"It is a sturdy wooden ladder large enough for a giant."
extra {"fresco", "frescos"}
"The frescos on the ceiling depict the world, pierced by the bite of a giant
mosquito, who is sucking the life from it. You shiver when you think of what
hell Ulchonix would create with your world if given the chance."
extra {"brazers"}
"The brazers glow with a dull golden light, but give off no heat. They are too
massive to be moved."
extra {"$drink blood"}
"From that font, with all the mosquitos in it? No way."
end


			spot_garden
names {"spotlight garden"}
title "A spotlight garden."
descr
"     This dirt floored chamber must be along the western edge of the pyramid,
as the west wall sweeps steeply up at an angle. A row of holes in the wall,
high out of reach, offer a tantalizing glimpse of the outside. Beams of light
fall into the room through those holes, allowing some sparse plants to grow
in the meager flicker.  A pool of blood lies along the northern wall of this
strange garden ... you can see something murky inside of it. A door leads
to the east."
movement SECT_INSIDE
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_TELEPORT, UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
east to gold_hall open {EX_OPEN_CLOSE} keyword {"door"};
down to blood_tube open {EX_OPEN_CLOSE} keyword {"tube"};
extra {"holes", "hole"}
"The holes are far too high up the wall for you to reach. Even if you could
reach them, it looks like it would be a tough squeeze through them."
extra {"blood", "pool", "tube"}
"You can see a pipe just under the surface of the blood pool. You could
definitely reach into the pool to open the tube and could probably swim down
through it (if you could hold your breath long enough)."
extra {"spotlights", "lights"}
"Falling from the holes in the wall, sunlight... so near and yet so far. Some
sturdy plants grow in the small circles of sunlight."
extra {"plants", "plant"}
"Some of these plants actually look unusual, some twisted little gnomes
reaching for the light. Others look like the canopy of jungle that you
remember surrounds this pyramid."
end


			blood_tube
names {"blood tube"}
title "Blood-filled tube"
descr
"     You are holding your breath in a narrow stone tube filled with blood.
There is no air here, and if you are going to swim somewhere, you better swim
there fast.  You can see the surface of the blood pool above, and the tube
taskes a twist to the north. The bloods looks seething with disease."
movement SECT_UNDER_WATER
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_TELEPORT, UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
special SFUN_DEATH_ROOM "10"
special SFUN_FORCE_MOVE time PULSE_SEC * 30
"lostlands/blood_pit!You are sucked down through a drain."
   time WAIT_SEC*100 bits SFB_RANTIME
north to u_loot;
up to spot_garden;
end

			u_loot
names {"ulchonix's loot", "treasury"}
title "Ulchonix's Treasury"
descr
"     Emerging from the blood tube, you are shocked to find yourself within
the treasury of the God of Jungle Fever.  Frescos cover every wall, depicting
Ulchonix and his lizard-men Sleestak warriors washing an entire world in blood
and disease.  The frescos all seem to stare at the end of the tube of blood
leading back down."
movement SECT_INSIDE
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_TELEPORT, UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
down to blood_tube;
end


			blood_pit
names {"blood pit", "pit"}
title "The pit of blood"
descr
"     You have emerged into a deep pit, almost full of blood. You scissor kick
your legs, keeping your head above blood. The ceiling lies nearly 5 feet above
your head, well out of reach. A massive obsidian spike penetrates up from the
blood, with strange inscriptions on its face. There are no obvious exits."
movement SECT_WATER_SWIM
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_TELEPORT, UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
up to gold_hall open {EX_OPEN_CLOSE, EX_CLOSED, EX_HIDDEN} keyword {"rift"};
SECRET_DOOR_DIFFICULTY (UP, 45)
extra {"spike"}
"The spike is made from smooth obsidian and more than large enough to impale a
person. You're lucky you didn't materialize directly on it! There is no way to
climb the spike. Strange inscriptions cover the surface of the spike."
extra {"inscriptions", "inscription", "$read"}
" Carved upon the obsidian spike are the words:
    ' The rift between us, gulf of blood,
      Shall pour from me in a hidden flood.
      If from the blood you should arise,
      Search blood again to reach the prize. '
"
extra {"blood"}
"You are 'treading water' in warm blood. You have no idea how deep the shaft
is, but you cannot feel any firm bottom."
extra {"ceiling"}
"You take a jump upwards, but the ceiling is well out of reach. You must be
missing something.... there must be a way out!"
extra {"walls"}
"They are smooth and slippery with blood and offer no sign of exits."
extra {"$drink blood"}
"Your head dips below the surface and blood pours into your mouth like a flood
into a canyon rift."
end

			enscroll_room
names {"enscroll room"}
title "The Divine Enscrolling Room"
descr
"     You are at the top of the ladder in a dark vaulted chamber of dark
obsidian, polished to a shine. A stone railing lies on one side, with a
massive book on a stand. The shiny black surfaces of the rooms must be playing
tricks on your eyes, because it seems as if there is a dancing blue flame
directly over your head, although you feel no heat."
movement SECT_INSIDE
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_TELEPORT, UNIT_FL_MAGIC, UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
down to gold_hall;
up to lag open {EX_OPEN_CLOSE, EX_CLOSED, EX_HIDDEN} keyword {"portal"};
SECRET_DOOR_DIFFICULTY (UP, 50)
extra {"portal"}
"If you defocus your eyes, you can make out a crude portal in the flicking
flames above you, leading into another dimension."
extra {"flames", "flame"}
"The flames look mystical, as if concealing a portal into another dimension."
extra {"bookstand", "stand"}
"It is carved from a massive block of the obsidian floor and is inscribed with
the name 'Venom'."
extra {"book"}
"This massive spellbook is turned to an arcane spell. You have difficulty
understanding it - this demi-god works strange spells - but you realize with
a chill that it has something to do with spreading infection through some kind
of quasi-plane called 'Lag Space'. "
end


			lag
names {"lag space", "lag"}
title "Lagspace"
descr
"     You have entered into a strange plane, somewhere beyond the world that
you have known, in a space made up of stolen moments and
glowing stars. Pulses of light spread out in all directions ... if you only you were as
unsubstantial, so that you could sail away with the lights. One section of
lights, however, pulses with a strange color and pattern, like the heartbeat
of a fever victim. It's colors spread out like a wound through Lagspace."
movement SECT_INSIDE
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_TELEPORT, UNIT_FL_MAGIC, UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
east to disease_p open {EX_OPEN_CLOSE, EX_CLOSED, EX_HIDDEN} keyword {"wound"};
SECRET_DOOR_DIFFICULTY (EAST, 30)
extra {"wound", "weave"}
"It looks like some kind of seething sore on the network, like a deep wound
pulsing with gangrene. Before your very eyes, you see it surge forth, becoming
even larger."
extra {"lights", "electrons"}
"This vast network of energy looks like a world unto itself. A flashing light
zooms by your face and you wish that you could join it in it's dance."
extra {"sections"}
"One section of the lagscape pulses with strange throbbing colors, like a
wound."
end


			u_limbo
names {"ulchonix's limbo", "ulimbo"}
title "Ulchonix's limbo"
descr
"    How did you end up in this limbo, created by the blood sacrifices of a
thousand tribesmen? Amazing the difficulties you can get in when you go
random teleporting around, huh? This timeless, shifting place has no exits."
movement SECT_INSIDE
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
extra {""}
"Didn't I tell you that there is nothing else to see?"
end

			lost_room
names {"lostspace", "lost"}
title "the Space of the Lost"
descr
"     You have arrived in strange, timeless place - the place that all lost
things end up. You can see no exits from the featureless gray landscape."
movement SECT_INSIDE
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
extra {""}
"Didn't I tell you that there is nothing else to see?"
end


/*----------- Dinosaur Area ---------*/

			pri_swamp1
names {"primordial swamp"}
title "The primordial swamp"
descr
"    This massive primordial swamp drains into a delta to the north.
Strange insects and primitive mosses choke the water dredged ground, making
movement difficult. The ground only firm enough to travel to the south."
movement SECT_SWAMP
north to swamp_drain;
south to pri_swamp2;
end

			pri_swamp2
names {"primordial swamp"}
title "The primordial swamp"
descr
"    The primordial swamp grows thicker here - with each step your feet sink
below the algae filled ooze into the mud. A large sinkhole lies to the west."
movement SECT_SWAMP
north to pri_swamp1;
south to pri_swamp3;
east to pri_swamp4;
extra {"sinkhole"}
"The sinkhole is flooded with water, who knows how deep. You'll have to
travel a different direction."
end

			pri_swamp3
names {"primordial swamp"}
title "The primordial swamp"
descr
"    The thick primordial swamp joins a thicker, drier jungle to the east.
To the west, you see the edge of lava flow from the far-off volcano. Thick
impassable jungle stretched to the south."
movement SECT_SWAMP
west to lava2;
east to pri_jungle1;
north to pri_swamp2;
end

			pri_swamp4
names {"primordial swamp"}
title "The primordial swamp"
descr
"    You are trudging along a muddy ridge in a primordial swamp. Deeper swamp,
impassible, lies to the north and south. The ridge continues to the west and
rises into a marsh to the east."
movement SECT_SWAMP
west to pri_swamp2;
east to pri_marsh2;
end

			lava1
names {"lava fields"}
title "Hot lava fields"
descr
"    The primordial swamps and jungles haven been burnt to ashes by the thick
lava flow coming form the erupting volcano to the west. The heat from the
molten rock is so hot, that you can only move south."
movement SECT_MOUNTAIN
south to lava2;
end

			lava2
names {"lava fields"}
title "Hot lava fields"
descr
"    The primordial swamps and jungles haven been burnt to ashes by the thick
lava flow coming form the erupting volcano to the west. The heat from the
molten rock is so hot, that you can only move north and south along the edge
of the flow."
movement SECT_MOUNTAIN
north to lava1;
east to pri_swamp3;
south to lava3;
end

			lava3
names {"lava fields"}
title "Hot lava fields"
descr
"    The primordial swamps and jungles haven been burnt to ashes by the thick
lava flow coming form the erupting volcano to the west. The heat from the
molten rock is so hot, that you can only move north."
movement SECT_MOUNTAIN
north to lava2;
end

			pri_jungle1
names {"primordial jungle"}
title "The primordial jungle"
descr
"    This narrow path through thick, primordial jungle ends to the west
on the banks of a thick, murky swamp.  The path slopes back, slightly uphill,
to the east."
movement SECT_SWAMP
west to pri_swamp3;
east to pri_jungle3;
end

			pri_jungle2
names {"primordial jungle"}
title "The primordial jungle"
descr
"    This broad path through the primordial jungle ends to the west in a broad
clearing. The path to the east looks like it was made by a large animals, with
broken and trampled foliage everywhere."
movement SECT_SWAMP
east to pri_jungle4;
west to pri_clearing;
end

			pri_jungle3
names {"primordial jungle"}
title "The primordial jungle"
descr
"    You are on a narrow trail through thick, primordial jungle. The trail
continues east and west. To the south, you can see a wider trail, as if made
by a stampede of large animals. To the north the jungle thins out into a
marsh."
movement SECT_SWAMP
north to pri_marsh2;
south to pri_jungle4;
east to pri_jungle5;
west to pri_jungle1;
end

			pri_jungle4
names {"primordial jungle"}
title "The primordial jungle"
descr
"    You are at one end of a broad path through the jungle stretching to
the west. The jungle looks like it has been trampled by large beasts. Some
has erected a clever hunting blind to the east."
movement SECT_SWAMP
north to pri_jungle3;
east to pri_blind;
west to pri_jungle2;
end

			pri_jungle5
names {"primordial jungle"}
title "The primordial jungle"
descr
"    You are on a narrow path through thick primordial jungle. Massive
fern like plants coil above you and strange sounds echo from deep within the
foliage. Down the trail to the east you see the massive gold gates of the
jungle village. The trail continues west."
movement SECT_SWAMP
east to out_gold_gate;
west to pri_jungle3;
end

			pri_jungle6
names {"primordial jungle"}
title "The primordial jungle"
descr
"    You are in a stretch of primordial jungle at the base of a short
muddy cliff. You can easily move into a deep gully to the east or into the
marshes to the north, but the mud makes the cliff to the south unscalable."
movement SECT_SWAMP
east to pri_gully1;
north to pri_marsh3;
end

			pri_marsh1
names {"primordial marsh"}
title "The primordial marsh"
descr
"    This is as deep into the primordial swamp as you can travel. The ground
becomes increasingly soft, as strange gases bubble up through the mud. The
shore of the marsh stretches to the south and east."
movement SECT_SWAMP
south to pri_marsh2;
east to pri_marsh3;
end

			pri_marsh2
names {"primordial marsh"}
title "The primordial marsh"
descr
"    You are on the edge of a primordial swamp. The vegetation becomes
thicker to the west and you could get deeper into the swamp to the north.
The jungle spreads out along the southern bank."
movement SECT_SWAMP
west to pri_swamp4;
north to pri_marsh1;
south to pri_jungle3;
end

			pri_marsh3
names {"primordial marsh"}
title "The primordial marsh"
descr
"    The marsh coast ends here in impassible mud swamps. You can duck back
into the jungle to the south, or travel deeper into the marsh to the west."
movement SECT_SWAMP
south to pri_jungle6;
west to pri_marsh1;
end

			pri_gully1
names {"primordial gully"}
title "The primordial gully"
descr
"    You are in a rocky gully at the base of the village walls. You can see
the gold gate to the village south of here, at the top of a cliff you could
never hope to climb. The primordial jungle lies to the west and the gully goes
deeper to the north."
movement SECT_MOUNTAIN
north to pri_gully2;
west to pri_jungle6;
end

			pri_gully2
names {"primordial gully"}
title "The primordial gully"
descr
"    You have come to the end of the gully at the base of the village wall.
The high rocky walls are unscalable. The gully stretches to the south towards
the jungle."
movement SECT_MOUNTAIN
south to pri_gully1;
end

			pri_clearing
names {"primordial clearing"}
title "The primordial clearing"
descr
"    You have burst from the jungle into a secluded clearing. Animals have
grazed away most of the foliage in this area, although the only exit from
the clearing is east."
movement SECT_FIELD
east to pri_jungle2;
end

			pri_blind
names {"primordial blind"}
title "A blind in the primordial jungle"
descr
"    Someone has cleared a section of the jungle into a hunters blind. You
have a great view down the wide jungle path and feel well hidden from any
roaming beasts. The blind opens into the jungle to the west."
movement SECT_SWAMP
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_MOB}
west to pri_jungle4;
end


/*----------------------MOBILES-----------------------*/
%mobiles


/*--------------Environmental Imps-----------------*/

			familiar1
names {"familiar","daemon"}
title "the tiny winged daemon"
descr
"A tiny winged demon, no more than a foot tall, stares at you intently."
extra {}
"This little guy looks like he could punch a wallop. You remember all the
horror stories you have heard of hapless adventurers messing with a wizard's
familiar only to meet some horrible death. Perhaps you should leave this
daemon alone and allow it to complete it's mission for it's master."
level 10
position POSITION_SLEEPING
race RACE_OTHER_CREATURE
alignment 0
weight 2
NATURAL_DEF(WPN_BITE, ARM_HLEATHER)
sex SEX_NEUTRAL
capacity 1000
romflags {CHAR_DETECT_INVISIBLE}
MSET_ABILITY (20,15,10,10,15,15,15,0)
MSET_WEAPON (8,8,8,8,8,0)
MSET_SPELL (4,4,4,20,4,4,4,4,4,4,4)
manipulate MANIPULATE_TAKE
special SFUN_COMBAT_MAGIC_HEAL "c random teleport"
special SFUN_COMBAT_POISON
special SFUN_PAIN_INIT time WAIT_SEC*15 bits SFB_RANTIME
" 100 I1000cabalist@
  110 I2000statue@
  120 Ctake all@
  130 Cexit corpse@
  140 Ccast controlled teleport bob@
  150 Gudgaard/temple@
  160 J2000@
 1000 Cstand@
 1005 R1010,80@
 1007 Cemote looks around curiously, as though sensing something.@
